Kubernetes

Need to install docker
 yum install docker -y && systemctl start docker
 
Need to install minikube
curl -LO https://github.com/kubernetes/minikube/releases/latest/download/minikube-linux-amd64
sudo install minikube-linux-amd64 /usr/local/bin/minikube && rm minikube-linux-amd64

minikube version--> to check the version
minikube start --driver=docker --force  -->  to start the minikube
minikube status--> to check the status

CLI(Command Line Interface)
kubectl -- it is a CLI tool for kubernetes that starts with kubectl for all commands

To install kubectl
 go to browser -- serach with kubectl instal
  curl -LO "https://dl.k8s.io/release/$(curl -L -s https://dl.k8s.io/release/stable.txt)/bin/linux/amd64/kubectl"--> to install kubectl
  chmod +x kubectl--> to give the x permissions
   mv kubectl /usr/local/bin/--> need to move kubectl to default path, then only it'll show as installed
   kubectl version--> to check whether installed or not
   
Need to cretae a pod--> 
Imperative---- will create by using commands
Delarative---- will create by using manifest files (In real time we use this)

 kubectl api-resources--. to check th elist of resources
 
cretae a pod in imperative way
  kubectl run mypod --image=nginx--> to cretae a pod
  kubectl get pods--> to check the pods
  
cretae a pod in Delarative way
  vim pod.yml
    ---
apiVersion:v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: devops-pod
spec:
  containers:
    - name: mycontainer
      image: shaikmustafa/dm
      ports:
        - containerPort: 80
		
kubectl create -f pod.yml--> to execute the pod file
kubectl get po -o wide--> to check the Ip address and node details
kubectl get po -o yaml--> to check the Ip address and node details pf POD in yaml format
kubectl get po -o json--> to check the Ip address and node details pf POD in json format
kubectl get po mypod -o yaml--. to check specific pod Ip address and node details
kubectl describe pod mypod--> to get complete info about pod
kubectl delete pod mypod--> to delete the pod
kubectl delete pod --all--> to delete all the pods
kubectl get po --> to check the pods



     
